<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<meta name="description" content="A complete record of every tax and fee increase enacted under Governor Mills since 2019. 32 increases. No spin.">
<title>32 Times: Maine Tax Tracker | Lead Maine</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Barlow+Condensed:wght@400;700;800;900&family=Lora:ital,wght@0,400;0,600;1,400&family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
:root {
  --bg:        #FFFFFF;
  --bg2:       #F7F7F5;
  --bg3:       #EEECEA;
  --text:      #1A1A1A;
  --muted:     #6B7280;
  --border:    #E2E0DC;
  --red:       #C8281F;
  --gold:      #9A6F1A;
  --cat-consumer: #B45309;
  --cat-income:   #B91C1C;
  --cat-payroll:  #7C3AED;
  --cat-business: #1D4ED8;
  --cat-healthcare:#0F766E;
  --cat-fee:      #4F46E5;
  --cat-fiscal:   #374151;
  --radius:    5px;
  --mono: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
  --serif: 'Lora', Georgia, serif;
  --cond: 'Barlow Condensed', sans-serif;
}
*, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
body {
  background: var(--bg);
  color: var(--text);
  font-family: var(--serif);
  font-size: 16px;
  line-height: 1.6;
}
a { color: var(--gold); text-decoration: none; }
a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

/* ===== MASTHEAD ===== */
.masthead {
  background: #FFFFFF;
  position: sticky;
  top: 0;
  z-index: 100;
  border-bottom: 2px solid var(--red);
  box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
}
.masthead-inner {
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 1.5rem;
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: auto 1fr auto;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 2rem;
  height: 56px;
}
.masthead-brand {
  display: flex;
  align-items: baseline;
  gap: 0.75rem;
}
.masthead-count {
  font-family: var(--cond);
  font-weight: 900;
  font-size: 2.2rem;
  line-height: 1;
  color: var(--red);
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
}
.masthead-title {
  font-family: var(--cond);
  font-weight: 700;
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--text);
  line-height: 1.2;
}
.masthead-title span { color: var(--muted); display: block; font-weight: 400; }
.masthead-stats {
  display: flex;
  gap: 0;
  align-items: center;
}
.mstat {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  border-left: 1px solid var(--border);
  padding: 0 1.25rem;
}
.mstat-val {
  font-family: var(--cond);
  font-weight: 800;
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  line-height: 1;
  color: var(--red);
}
.mstat-label {
  font-family: var(--cond);
  font-size: 0.6rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--muted);
  white-space: nowrap;
}
.masthead-nav {
  display: flex;
  gap: 1.5rem;
  font-family: var(--cond);
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
}
.masthead-nav a { color: var(--muted); transition: color 0.2s; }
.masthead-nav a:hover { color: var(--text); text-decoration: none; }

/* ===== SWATCH BAR ===== */
.swatch-bar { height: 4px; display: flex; gap: 2px; }
.swatch { flex: 1; }

/* ===== FILTER BAR ===== */
.filter-bar {
  background: var(--bg2);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  position: sticky;
  top: 60px;
  z-index: 50;
}
.filter-bar-inner {
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0.55rem 1.5rem;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 0.5rem;
}
.cat-chips { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.35rem; }
.cat-chip {
  font-family: var(--cond);
  font-size: 0.73rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  padding: 0.25rem 0.7rem;
  border-radius: 20px;
  cursor: pointer;
  border: 1px solid transparent;
  transition: all 0.12s;
  user-select: none;
  line-height: 1.4;
}
.cat-chip.active { color: #fff; }
.cat-chip:not(.active) { background: #fff; color: var(--muted); border-color: var(--border); }
.cat-chip:not(.active):hover { color: var(--text); border-color: #aaa; }
.cat-chip[data-cat="all"].active      { background: var(--red); border-color: var(--red); }
.cat-chip[data-cat="consumer"].active  { background: var(--cat-consumer); border-color: var(--cat-consumer); }
.cat-chip[data-cat="income"].active    { background: var(--cat-income); border-color: var(--cat-income); }
.cat-chip[data-cat="payroll"].active   { background: var(--cat-payroll); border-color: var(--cat-payroll); }
.cat-chip[data-cat="business"].active  { background: var(--cat-business); border-color: var(--cat-business); }
.cat-chip[data-cat="healthcare"].active{ background: var(--cat-healthcare); border-color: var(--cat-healthcare); }
.cat-chip[data-cat="fee"].active       { background: var(--cat-fee); border-color: var(--cat-fee); }
.cat-chip[data-cat="fiscal"].active    { background: var(--cat-fiscal); border-color: var(--cat-fiscal); }
.filter-count {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  color: var(--muted);
  white-space: nowrap;
}
.filter-count span { color: var(--text); font-weight: 500; }

/* ===== TABLE ===== */
.table-wrap {
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 1.5rem 2rem;
}
table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.875rem; }
thead th {
  font-family: var(--cond);
  font-size: 0.67rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--muted);
  padding: 0.65rem 0.75rem;
  text-align: left;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  background: var(--bg);
  position: sticky;
  top: 93px;
  z-index: 10;
  white-space: nowrap;
}
thead th:first-child { width: 44px; }
tbody tr {
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: background 0.1s;
}
tbody tr:hover { background: var(--bg2); }
tbody tr.is-open { background: #FEF9F0; }
td { padding: 0.7rem 0.75rem; vertical-align: top; }
td:first-child {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  color: var(--muted);
  white-space: nowrap;
  padding-top: 0.85rem;
}
.item-name {
  font-family: var(--serif);
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--text);
  line-height: 1.3;
  margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
}
.item-preview {
  font-family: var(--serif);
  font-style: italic;
  font-size: 0.78rem;
  color: var(--muted);
  line-height: 1.4;
}
.cat-badge {
  display: inline-block;
  font-family: var(--cond);
  font-size: 0.63rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  padding: 0.18rem 0.5rem;
  border-radius: 3px;
  color: #fff;
  white-space: nowrap;
}
.change-val { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.45; }
.effective-val { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.74rem; color: var(--muted); white-space: nowrap; }
.revenue-val { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.74rem; color: var(--gold); }
.revenue-na { color: var(--muted); }
.source-val { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.68rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.5; }
.expand-row { display: none; }
.expand-row td {
  background: #FFFDF7;
  padding: 0.9rem 0.9rem 0.9rem 3rem;
  border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border);
}
.expand-row p {
  font-family: var(--serif);
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  color: #4B5563;
  line-height: 1.75;
  max-width: 720px;
}
.expand-row p strong { color: var(--text); }
.expand-icon {
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.65rem;
  color: var(--muted);
  transition: transform 0.15s;
  display: inline-block;
  margin-right: 4px;
}
.is-open .expand-icon { transform: rotate(90deg); color: var(--red); }
.no-results {
  text-align: center; padding: 3rem;
  font-family: var(--serif); font-style: italic; color: var(--muted); display: none;
}

/* ===== LOWER ===== */
.lower-sections {
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 2rem 1.5rem 3rem;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 2rem;
  align-items: start;
}
.design-prompt-box {
  background: #FFFDF3;
  border: 1px dashed #C9A84C;
  border-radius: var(--radius);
  padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
}
.design-prompt-box h3 {
  font-family: var(--cond);
  font-size: 0.7rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.12em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--gold);
  margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.4rem;
}
.design-prompt-box h3::before {
  content: '';
  display: inline-block;
  width: 5px; height: 5px;
  background: var(--gold);
  border-radius: 50%;
}
.design-prompt-box p { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 0.85rem; }
.prompt-code {
  background: #1A1A1A;
  border-radius: 4px;
  padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
  font-family: var(--mono);
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  color: #C9B67E;
  line-height: 1.7;
  white-space: pre-wrap;
  word-break: break-word;
}
.sources-box {
  padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  background: var(--bg2);
  border: 1px solid var(--border);
  border-radius: var(--radius);
}
.sources-box h3 {
  font-family: var(--cond);
  font-size: 0.7rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.12em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--muted);
  margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
}
.sources-box p { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }

/* ===== FOOTER ===== */
footer {
  border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  font-family: var(--cond);
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  color: var(--muted);
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}

/* ===== RESPONSIVE ===== */
@media (max-width: 900px) {
  .masthead-stats { display: none; }
  .lower-sections { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .col-revenue { display: none; }
}
@media (max-width: 680px) {
  .col-effective { display: none; }
  .masthead-inner { grid-template-columns: auto 1fr; }
  .masthead-nav { display: none; }
}
@media (max-width: 480px) { .col-change { display: none; } }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<header class="masthead">
  <div class="masthead-inner">
    <div class="masthead-brand">
      <div class="masthead-count">32</div>
      <div class="masthead-title">Times Augusta Raised Taxes<span>or Fees Since 2019</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="masthead-stats">
      <div class="mstat"><div class="mstat-val">#5</div><div class="mstat-label">Most Taxed State</div></div>
      <div class="mstat"><div class="mstat-val">65%</div><div class="mstat-label">Spending Growth Since 2018</div></div>
      <div class="mstat"><div class="mstat-val">$292M</div><div class="mstat-label">Rainy Day Fund Drained</div></div>
      <div class="swatch-bar" id="swatchBar" aria-hidden="true"></div>
</header>

<div class="filter-bar">
  <div class="filter-bar-inner">
    <div class="cat-chips" role="group" aria-label="Filter by category">
      <button class="cat-chip active" data-cat="all">All (32)</button>
      <button class="cat-chip" data-cat="consumer">Consumer / Sales</button>
      <button class="cat-chip" data-cat="income">Income Tax</button>
      <button class="cat-chip" data-cat="payroll">Payroll</button>
      <button class="cat-chip" data-cat="business">Business</button>
      <button class="cat-chip" data-cat="healthcare">Healthcare</button>
      <button class="cat-chip" data-cat="fee">Fees &amp; Licenses</button>
      <button class="cat-chip" data-cat="fiscal">Fiscal Policy</button>
    </div>
    <div class="filter-count">Showing <span id="visibleCount">32</span> of 32</div>
  </div>
</div>

<main>
<div class="table-wrap">
  <table id="trackerTable" aria-label="Tax and fee increases under Governor Mills since 2019">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>#</th>
        <th>Increase</th>
        <th>Category</th>
        <th class="col-change">Change</th>
        <th class="col-effective">Effective</th>
        <th class="col-revenue">Revenue Impact</th>
        <th>Legislative Source</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody id="trackerBody"></tbody>
  </table>
  <p class="no-results" id="noResults">No increases match this filter.</p>
</div>

<script>
const CAT_COLORS = {
  consumer:   '#B45309',
  income:     '#B91C1C',
  payroll:    '#7C3AED',
  business:   '#1D4ED8',
  healthcare: '#0F766E',
  fee:        '#4F46E5',
  fiscal:     '#374151'
};
const CAT_LABELS = {
  consumer:   'Consumer',
  income:     'Income Tax',
  payroll:    'Payroll',
  business:   'Business',
  healthcare: 'Healthcare',
  fee:        'Fee / License',
  fiscal:     'Fiscal Policy'
};

const items = [
  { id:1,  cat:'consumer',   name:'Cigarette / Tobacco Tax',                    preview:'First increase in 20 years. Party-line Democratic vote.',                                        change:'$2.00 &#8594; $3.50/pack (+75%)',                  effective:'Jan 5, 2026',        revenue:'~$55.5M/yr',    source:'PL 2025, c. 388, Part E',           details:'First tobacco tax increase in 20 years. Per-cigarette rate: 10 cents to 17.5 cents. Smokeless tobacco: $2.02/oz to $3.54/oz. Vapes, pouches, other nicotine products: 43% to 75% of wholesale price. Passed on a party-line Democratic vote. The final rate exceeded Governor Mills\' original $1.00/pack proposal. Revenue: about $111M over the biennium (MPI/State). Nearly 30% of adults earning under $25,000/yr smoke, vs. 7.4% of those earning $50,000+.' },
  { id:2,  cat:'consumer',   name:'Streaming Services Tax (New, 5.5%)',          preview:'Netflix, Hulu, Spotify, podcasts. Previously untaxed.',                                          change:'0% &#8594; 5.5% (new)',                            effective:'Jan 1, 2026',        revenue:'~$6.5M/yr (est.)', source:'PL 2025, c. 388, Part G',        details:'Digital audiovisual and digital audio services, including Netflix, Hulu, Spotify, and podcasts, are now subject to Maine\'s 5.5% sales tax. Previously untaxed. Estimated to generate about $13M through 2027 (MPI/State), roughly $6.5M/yr. Governor Mills proposed this tax multiple times before it passed.' },
  { id:3,  cat:'consumer',   name:'Canned Software / Electronic Products',       preview:'Software subscriptions, app downloads, electronic transfers. Previously untaxed.',                change:'0% &#8594; 5.5% (newly taxable)',                  effective:'Jan 1, 2025',        revenue:'Not separately scored', source:'LD 1216 / PL 2021, c. 245',   details:'Sale, lease, rental, or license of canned computer software or electronically transferred products is now treated as a taxable sale of tangible personal property. No standalone revenue estimate was published for this provision.' },
  { id:4,  cat:'consumer',   name:'Cannabis Sales Tax',                          preview:'Adult-use sales tax raised 40%.',                                                                  change:'10% &#8594; 14% (+40%)',                           effective:'Jan 1, 2026',        revenue:'~$3-8M/yr (est.)', source:'PL 2025, c. 388, Part F',        details:'The adult-use cannabis sales tax rate increased from 10% to 14%, a 40% rate increase. Cannabis excise taxes on specific products were separately reduced. Estimates vary: MPI cites about $6M over the biennium; other budget documents put the figure higher (up to ~$15M/biennium).' },
  { id:5,  cat:'consumer',   name:'Real Estate Transfer Tax (sales over $1M)',   preview:'Rate nearly tripled on the portion of sales above $1 million.',                                  change:'$2.20 &#8594; $6.00 per $500 (+173%)',             effective:'Nov 1, 2025',        revenue:'~$13M/yr (est.)', source:'PL 2025, c. 388, Part V',         details:'The transfer tax rate on property value exceeding $1 million increased from $2.20 per $500 to $6.00 per $500. Thirty percent of new revenue routed to the Maine State Housing Authority. No standalone figure was published; estimate derived from the state aggregate. More than 1,000 Maine homes sold for $1 million or more in 2024.' },
  { id:6,  cat:'consumer',   name:'Service Provider Tax Base Expanded',          preview:'Cable, telecom, fabrication services folded into standard sales tax; new digital services captured.',change:'6% SPT repealed; base folded into 5.5% sales tax', effective:'Jan 1, 2026',      revenue:'Not separately scored', source:'PL 2025, c. 388, Part G',    details:'The 6% Service Provider Tax on cable/satellite, telecom, fabrication, and rental-purchase agreements was repealed and folded into the 5.5% standard sales and use tax. Net effect: the rate dropped 0.5% on services already taxed, but the base expanded to capture streaming and other digital services. Not separately scored net of the rate cut.' },
  { id:7,  cat:'consumer',   name:'Lease-Stream Taxation Timing Changed',        preview:'Sales tax on leased property now applies to each periodic payment rather than upfront.',          change:'Taxation: upfront &#8594; periodic payments',      effective:'Jan 1, 2025',        revenue:'Not separately scored', source:'PL 2023, c. 412',            details:'Sales tax on leased or rented tangible personal property now applies to each periodic payment rather than to the upfront purchase price. A timing change in collection; not separately scored.' },
  { id:8,  cat:'consumer',   name:'Tobacco Products Definition Expanded',        preview:'Synthetic nicotine products captured before the 2026 rate hike.',                                 change:'Definition expanded to include synthetic nicotine', effective:'Aug 9, 2024',        revenue:'Bundled in #1',   source:'PL 2023, c. 613',                 details:'The definition of "tobacco products" was amended to include products containing nicotine whether natural or artificial, capturing synthetic nicotine products before the 2026 rate increase. Revenue effect is bundled into the tobacco tax line (#1).' },
  { id:9,  cat:'income',     name:'2% Income Tax Surcharge on Income Over $1M',  preview:'New top marginal rate 9.15%, retroactive to Jan 1, 2026.',                                       change:'7.15% &#8594; 9.15% (income over $1M)',           effective:'Jan 1, 2026 (retro)', revenue:'~$74M/yr',      source:'LD 2212 (signed Apr 10, 2026)',      details:'A new 2% surcharge taking Maine\'s top marginal rate from 7.15% to 9.15%, retroactive to January 1, 2026. Thresholds: $1,000,000 for single and head-of-household filers, $1,500,000 for married-joint and surviving-spouse filers, and $750,000 for married-filing-separately. About 2,600 filers; roughly $74M/yr ($140M+ over the biennium). Note on the PTET: owners of pass-through businesses can elect the Pass-Through Entity Tax, under which the entity pays at 7.15% and owners receive a 90% credit, but resident owners may still owe the 2% surtax on income above the threshold. The surcharge is not fully avoided.' },
  { id:10, cat:'payroll',    name:'Paid Family and Medical Leave: New 1% Payroll Tax', preview:'Broadest new tax on working Mainers. Benefits began May 1, 2026, after 16 months of paying in.', change:'New 1% payroll tax (0.5% employer / 0.5% employee)', effective:'Jan 1, 2025', revenue:'~$300M+/yr (est.)', source:'Maine PFML Act',          details:'Maine\'s PFML program imposes a 1% payroll tax on wages up to the Social Security wage base ($176,100 in 2025). For employers with 15+ employees: 0.5% each. For employers with fewer than 15: only the employee\'s 0.5% is required. Tax began collecting January 1, 2025; benefits did not become available until May 1, 2026, a 16-month gap. Revenue flows to a dedicated PFML fund; program-wide premiums are estimated in the hundreds of millions per year.' },
  { id:11, cat:'business',   name:'BETR Eliminated for Retail Property',          preview:'Business Equipment Tax Reimbursement sunsetted for retail.',                                      change:'100% &#8594; 50% (CY2027), then 0% (CY2028+)',    effective:'CY2027',             revenue:'~$1-3M/yr (est.)', source:'LD 2212',                       details:'The 2026 supplemental budget sunsets the Business Equipment Tax Reimbursement (BETR) program for retail property: reimbursement drops to 50% for taxes paid on retail property in CY2027 and falls to zero for CY2028 and after. The overall BETR program had fallen to a forecast $16.8M in FY26 (DAFS); the retail share is small, so state savings are estimated at roughly $1-3M/yr.' },
  { id:12, cat:'business',   name:'Federal Tax Conformity Phased, Not Immediate',  preview:'Maine phases in OBBBA relief over years instead of granting it at once.',                        change:'Immediate federal relief &#8594; phased to 2027-2030', effective:'TY2025-2030',     revenue:'~$30M+/yr deferred (est.)', source:'LD 2212',                  details:'Maine conformed to some OBBBA items but phased others rather than granting them immediately. The higher standard deduction is partial for TY2026 and full only in TY2027; the charitable deduction for non-itemizers is 50% in TY2027 and full in TY2028; large-business R&E expensing phases in over TY2026-2030. Small-business R&E, the higher Section 179 expensing limits, and the Section 163(j) business interest deduction were conformed. Full standard-deduction conformity alone is worth more than $30M/yr (DAFS); the conformity package cost about $48M this biennium and $132M next (MECEP).' },
  { id:13, cat:'business',   name:'Decoupled from OBBBA Business & Investment Breaks', preview:'Maine opts out of federal 100% depreciation, Opportunity Zones, and small-business-stock gains.', change:'Decoupled from §168(n), §1400Z-2, §1202',      effective:'TY2025+',            revenue:'Part of decoupling package', source:'LD 2212',                 details:'The 2026 supplemental budget decouples Maine from three OBBBA business and investment breaks: the 100% depreciation election for qualified production property (IRC §168(n)) and continued decoupling from bonus depreciation; the Opportunity Zone capital gains deferral, exclusion, and 5-year basis step-up (IRC §1400Z-2, investments after Dec 31, 2026); and the Qualified Small Business Stock gain exclusion (IRC §1202, stock acquired after July 3, 2025). For Maine purposes these federal benefits are added back. Scored only as part of the decoupling package, which the legislature says avoided hundreds of millions per biennium (MECEP).' },
  { id:14, cat:'business',   name:'Employer Credit for FMLA Repealed',            preview:'Employer credit eliminated for tax years beginning Jan 1, 2026.',                                change:'Credit repealed',                                  effective:'Jan 1, 2026',        revenue:'<$1M/yr (est.)',  source:'LD 2212',                         details:'Maine\'s employer credit for family and medical leave was repealed for tax years beginning on or after January 1, 2026, removing a market-based incentive for employers to voluntarily offer leave benefits alongside the state PFML program. Small revenue effect, estimated under $1M/yr.' },
